# Given a filename, return the filepath. Default folder is the `data` folder in the current working directory.
get_path <- function(filename) {
  str_c(getwd(), "data", filename, sep = "/")
}

# Colors:
ISLR_blue <- "#176FC0"
ISLR_brown <- "#94340E"

# Return vector of the names of numeric columns in a data frame:
numeric_cols <- function(df) {
  is_numeric_cols <- map_lgl(df, is.numeric)
  return(names(df)[is_numeric_cols])
}

# Print accuracy, test rate and table of predicted labels and true labels:
test_rates <- function(predicted_label, test_label) {
  print(table(predicted_label, test_label))
  test_accuracy <- mean(predicted_label == test_label)*100
  test_error <- mean(predicted_label != test_label)*100
  print(str_interp("Test accuracy: ${round(test_accuracy, 2)}"))
  print(str_interp("Test error rate: ${round(test_error, 2)}"))
}

The model has poorer performance than the logistic regression and LDA models when predicting Up, and actually never predicts Down as the class.

KNN

set.seed(1)
k <- 1:100
knn_list <- map(k, 
                function(k) {
                    knn(train.X, test.X, train.Y, k = k)
                }
            )

knn_errors <- map_dbl(knn_list,
                      function(preds) {
                        100*round(1 - mean(preds == Direction.test), 4)
                      }
              )

paste0("Value of k with lowest test error: ", which.min(knn_errors), " (", min(knn_errors), "%)")
[1] "Value of k with lowest test error: 47 (38.46%)"
knn_errors_df <- data.frame(k, error = knn_errors)
ggplot(knn_errors_df) +
  geom_line(aes(k, error))

For KNN, a value of \(k=47\) has the lowest test error at 38.46%. However a value of \(k=12\) gives a comparably low test error of 39.42%:

knn_errors_df %>%

  ggtitle("x^2")

PlotPower <- function(x, a) {
  y <- Power3(x, a)
  g <- tibble(x, y) %>% 
    ggplot() +
    geom_line(aes(x, y))
  return(g)
}

p1 <- PlotPower(1:10, 2) + ggtitle("x^2")
p2 <- PlotPower(1:100, 3) + ggtitle("x^3")
p1 + p2
